article.story: JOHNSON CITY, Tenn. -- — Jaden Seymour scored 15 points as East Tennessee State beat Wofford 57-50 on Wednesday night. Seymour added five rebounds for the Buccaneers (13-11, 5-6 Southern Conference). Karon Boyd scored 14 points while going 3 of 8 and 8 of 10 from the free throw line, and added eight rebounds and three steals. Ebby Asamoah had 13 points and shot 5 for 14, including 3 for 11 from beyond the arc. The Terriers (13-11, 6-5) were led by Corey Tripp, who recorded 13 points and four steals. Jeremy Lorenz added nine points and two blocks for Wofford. Belal El Shakery also had eight points. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
